<p>A new website serves as a centralized source of information for &#8220;Bioethics Bowl,&#8221; a learning competition modeled after the popular Ethics Bowl events, but with a focus on issues in clinical, biomedical research, and healthcare ethics.<span id="more-56425"></span></p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="wp-image-56426 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/bioethics-bowl.png" alt="" width="631" height="320" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/bioethics-bowl.png 877w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/bioethics-bowl-300x152.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/bioethics-bowl-768x390.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/bioethics-bowl-400x203.png 400w" sizes="(max-width: 631px) 100vw, 631px" /></p>
<p><a href="https://www.bioethicsbowl.org/home" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The site</a> was created by <a href="https://cssh.northeastern.edu/faculty/mark-wells/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mark Wells</a> (Northeastern University).</p>
<p>He writes, &#8220;While Bioethics Bowls competitions have been running for years now, this is the first website to gather information about those competitions into one place.&#8221;</p>
<p>The site contains information about upcoming competitions, resources for running the competitions, and other information. You can check it out <a href="https://www.bioethicsbowl.org/home" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2026/02/02/a-new-hub-for-bioethics-bowl-information/">A New Hub for Bioethics Bowl Information</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>